            <title><![CDATA[Split Fiction Is The Good Time Everyone Needs Right Now]]></title>
            <link>https://kotaku.com/split-fiction-co-op-review-steam-early-game-of-the-year-1851768668</link>
            <guid>https://www.resetera.com/threads/split-fiction-is-the-good-time-everyone-needs-right-now.1129359/</guid>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[https://kotaku.com/split-fiction-co-op-review-steam-early-game-of-the-year-1851768668<br/><br/><div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><div><div><figure id="" data-id="7d0f07dc0f080b35eb79f9583d4f53c4" data-recommend-id="image://7d0f07dc0f080b35eb79f9583d4f53c4" data-format="jpg" data-width="905" data-height="509" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Split Fiction key art shows the main characters. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Split Fiction key art shows the main characters. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Hazelight Studios</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="7d0f07dc0f080b35eb79f9583d4f53c4" data-recommend-id="image://7d0f07dc0f080b35eb79f9583d4f53c4" data-format="jpg" data-width="905" data-height="509" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Split Fiction key art shows the main characters. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>EA and Hazelight’s latest co-op adventure, <em>Split Fiction</em>, is out now across Xbox, PlayStation, and PC. As with previous Hazelight games, like <em>It Takes Two</em>, <em>Split Fiction</em> is a co-op only experience that features a dazzling amount of gameplay mechanics. One moment you’ll be flying dragons and later you’ll be navigating a sci-fi pinball machine as a small robotic ball. Since its release, we’ve covered the game quite a bit. Here’s all of our coverage of what is proving to be one of EA’s biggest hits in many, many years.</p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="ee787a5e57ffdb37e10fce5890aacfc2" data-recommend-id="image://ee787a5e57ffdb37e10fce5890aacfc2" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="An image of Split Fiction's two main characters, one in a sci-fi setting and the other in a fantasy setting." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="An image of Split Fiction's two main characters, one in a sci-fi setting and the other in a fantasy setting." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->EA</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="ee787a5e57ffdb37e10fce5890aacfc2" data-recommend-id="image://ee787a5e57ffdb37e10fce5890aacfc2" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="An image of Split Fiction's two main characters, one in a sci-fi setting and the other in a fantasy setting." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://cdkeys.pxf.io/c/379647/1566025/18216?subId1=KT&amp;u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cdkeys.com%2Fsplit-fiction-xbox-series-x-s-ww&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://cdkeys.pxf.io/c/379647/1566025/18216?subId1=KT&amp;u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cdkeys.com%2Fsplit-fiction-xbox-series-x-s-ww" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><em>Split Fiction</em></a></span> is equal parts heartwarming tale and heart-pounding adventure, expertly blending sci-fi and fantasy into a creative cooperative journey unlike anything you’ve seen. Before you dive in with a friend or loved one, though, here are four things you should know about the game. — Billy Givens</p><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/split-fiction-co-op-action-ea-tips-1851767988&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/split-fiction-co-op-action-ea-tips-1851767988">Read More</a></span></p></div></div><div><figure id="" data-id="777e0fd01f81c069b9d725ca4bc9dfa6" data-recommend-id="image://777e0fd01f81c069b9d725ca4bc9dfa6" data-format="jpg" data-width="1581" data-height="885" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Mio and Zoe meet their new dragon babies." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Mio and Zoe meet their new dragon babies." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Hazelight Studios</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="777e0fd01f81c069b9d725ca4bc9dfa6" data-recommend-id="image://777e0fd01f81c069b9d725ca4bc9dfa6" data-format="jpg" data-width="1581" data-height="885" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Mio and Zoe meet their new dragon babies." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p>When I played Hazelight’s last game, <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/it-takes-two-the-best-co-op-game-of-the-year-is-comin-1847973764&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/it-takes-two-the-best-co-op-game-of-the-year-is-comin-1847973764"><em>It Takes Two</em></a></span><em>, </em>back in 2021, it was with an ex who’d had different ideas about where our relationship should go than I did. This made playing as a squabbling, estranged couple in a co-op platformer more fitting for that moment in my life than I could have anticipated. So it’s funny that Hazelight’s upcoming co-op game, <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://eneba-games.sjv.io/dO70QK&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://eneba-games.sjv.io/dO70QK" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><em>Split Fiction</em></a></span>, also feels timely, this one due to its obvious disdain for corporate slop and art theft at a time when nearly every creative field, including the one I work in now, is dealing with the fallout of AI. — Kenneth Shepard</p><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/split-fiction-preview-josef-fares-ai-hazelight-co-op-1851765494?_gl=1*hjzmou*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTc0MTQ1MzY0Ni4yNDAuMS4xNzQxNDU1MDcyLjYwLjAuMA..&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/split-fiction-preview-josef-fares-ai-hazelight-co-op-1851765494?_gl=1*hjzmou*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTc0MTQ1MzY0Ni4yNDAuMS4xNzQxNDU1MDcyLjYwLjAuMA..">Read More</a></span></p></div></div><div><figure id="" data-id="4f6aca65fedf1c2037e10cb7560ab3de" data-recommend-id="image://4f6aca65fedf1c2037e10cb7560ab3de" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="An image of Split Fiction's main characters in a sci-fi setting staring at a large opening in a simulation room." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="An image of Split Fiction's main characters in a sci-fi setting staring at a large opening in a simulation room." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->EA</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="4f6aca65fedf1c2037e10cb7560ab3de" data-recommend-id="image://4f6aca65fedf1c2037e10cb7560ab3de" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="An image of Split Fiction's main characters in a sci-fi setting staring at a large opening in a simulation room." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p>Hazelight Studios has once again brought a whole heap of co-op joy with its newest game, <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://cdkeys.pxf.io/c/379647/1566025/18216?subId1=KT&amp;u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cdkeys.com%2Fsplit-fiction-xbox-series-x-s-ww&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://cdkeys.pxf.io/c/379647/1566025/18216?subId1=KT&amp;u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cdkeys.com%2Fsplit-fiction-xbox-series-x-s-ww" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><em>Split Fiction</em></a></span>, which sends two players on a high-stakes quest across high fantasy and sci-fi settings. There are plenty of funny and heartfelt moments for you and a friend to experience in this adventure. But if you’re wondering how many hours of cooperative fun there is to be had, we’ve got the answer for you. Here’s how long it takes to beat <em>Split Fiction</em>. — Billy Givens</p><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/split-fiction-how-long-to-beat-co-op-ea-1851767987&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/split-fiction-how-long-to-beat-co-op-ea-1851767987">Read More</a></span></p></div></div><div><figure id="" data-id="c07b1b85a2736628e5bdb0b6fa5863e1" data-recommend-id="image://c07b1b85a2736628e5bdb0b6fa5863e1" data-format="jpg" data-width="1600" data-height="901" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="An image of a baby bird squawking in Split Fiction." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="An image of a baby bird squawking in Split Fiction." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->EA / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="c07b1b85a2736628e5bdb0b6fa5863e1" data-recommend-id="image://c07b1b85a2736628e5bdb0b6fa5863e1" data-format="jpg" data-width="1600" data-height="901" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="An image of a baby bird squawking in Split Fiction." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p>As you work your way through one of Zoe’s early fantasy levels in <em>Split Fiction</em>, you’ll come across a collection of baby birds in tiny nests. One of these little buddies hasn’t fully hatched yet, with only his poor little wings sticking out. But you can help him, while also helping yourself clear the bramble in your way. Solving this puzzle will be easy with our egg-cellent…You know what? No. I’m not letting myself be that guy who does stupid egg puns. Here’s how to crack the bird egg in <em>Split Fiction</em>. That’s it. That’s all you’re getting from me. — Billy Givens</p><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/split-fiction-how-to-crack-baby-bird-egg-puzzle-guide-1851767990&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/split-fiction-how-to-crack-baby-bird-egg-puzzle-guide-1851767990">Read More</a></span></p></div></div><div><figure id="" data-id="e7c291045c497b8b33f4f823a48d44e0" data-recommend-id="image://e7c291045c497b8b33f4f823a48d44e0" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->EA / Hazelight / Steam / Metacritic / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="e7c291045c497b8b33f4f823a48d44e0" data-recommend-id="image://e7c291045c497b8b33f4f823a48d44e0" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p>As I write this sentence, the latest co-op adventure game from Hazelight, <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/split-fiction-metacritic-female-protags-josef-fares-1851768392&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/split-fiction-metacritic-female-protags-josef-fares-1851768392"><em>Split Fiction</em></a></span><em>, </em>hasn’t even been out for 48 hours. Yet based on player count numbers, Metacritic rankings, reviews, and player ratings, it is already one of EA’s most successful and critically acclaimed games in years. And hopefully, EA and other publishers learn a thing or two from the co-op game’s success.  — Zack Zwiezen</p><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/split-fiction-success-metacritic-90-steam-players-ea-1851768495?_gl=1*1t5eii8*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTc0MTQ1MzY0Ni4yNDAuMS4xNzQxNDU1MDcyLjYwLjAuMA..&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/split-fiction-success-metacritic-90-steam-players-ea-1851768495?_gl=1*1t5eii8*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTc0MTQ1MzY0Ni4yNDAuMS4xNzQxNDU1MDcyLjYwLjAuMA..">Read More</a></span></p></div></div><div><figure id="" data-id="6005ee148d952a28f304e60754024212" data-recommend-id="image://6005ee148d952a28f304e60754024212" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Zoe and Mio look at something in the sky." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Zoe and Mio look at something in the sky." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-notes="" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Hazelight Studios / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="6005ee148d952a28f304e60754024212" data-recommend-id="image://6005ee148d952a28f304e60754024212" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Zoe and Mio look at something in the sky." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p>In the dozen or so hours a friend and I put into <em>Split Fiction</em>, the latest co-op game from <em>It Takes Two </em>developer Hazelight, it never seemed to run out of ideas. This latest release, with its marriage of fantasy and science fiction, still feels as fresh and inventive as <em>It Takes Two </em>and <em>A Way Out </em>did for their time, which is all the more impressive considering that the studio has been releasing these co-op adventures now for the better part of a decade. — Kenneth Shepard</p><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/split-fiction-review-hazelight-coop-game-it-takes-two-1851767470?_gl=1*12ua2ys*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTc0MTQ1MzY0Ni4yNDAuMS4xNzQxNDU1MDcyLjYwLjAuMA..&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/split-fiction-review-hazelight-coop-game-it-takes-two-1851767470?_gl=1*12ua2ys*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTc0MTQ1MzY0Ni4yNDAuMS4xNzQxNDU1MDcyLjYwLjAuMA..">Read More</a></span></p></div></div></div></div>]]></content:encoded>
